<div id="review_2935858381" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2935858381" />
    <a title="Beth Sponzilli" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/19530825-beth-sponzilli"><img alt="Beth Sponzilli" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1629997891p2/19530825.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2935858381?book_show_action=true">Oct 16, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Beth Sponzilli" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Beth Sponzilli" href="/user/show/19530825-beth-sponzilli">Beth Sponzilli</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/19530825-beth-sponzilli?shelf=18th-century">18th-century</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/19530825-beth-sponzilli?shelf=early-american">early-american</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/19530825-beth-sponzilli?shelf=pioneer">pioneer</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2935858381" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1578751739056344295">A story set in the years before and during the Revolutionary war in the Catskills of New York. A woman’s husband abandons his family one day and forever changes their lives. A struggling widow then tries to survive on her farm with the reputation of a abandoned wife. An interesting read but it did lack something.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


