<span id="freeTextContainer10625807134722659566">This is a spellbinding tale of pre-revolutionary (1769) America set in the Hudson River Valley. When the main character&apos;s lazy, hen-pecked husband disappears from their farm at the foot of the Catskill Mountains, she is left to survive with her two children in quite desperate conditions. I hesitate to say too much as I don&apos;t want to spoil it for others. Suffice it to say that Christine Wade has incorporated literary legend and reality in a very clever way. If you enjoy descriptive, lyrical writi</span>
  <span id="freeText10625807134722659566" style="display:none">This is a spellbinding tale of pre-revolutionary (1769) America set in the Hudson River Valley. When the main character's lazy, hen-pecked husband disappears from their farm at the foot of the Catskill Mountains, she is left to survive with her two children in quite desperate conditions. I hesitate to say too much as I don't want to spoil it for others. Suffice it to say that Christine Wade has incorporated literary legend and reality in a very clever way. If you enjoy descriptive, lyrical writing and like to read books as much for the beauty of the prose as the story, Seven Locks cannot be be beat. But the story is top-notch, too. A winner on both counts! Loved it!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="10625807134722659566" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

