<div id="review_532118909" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/532118909" />
    <a title="Gina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12123287-gina"><img alt="Gina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1345672613p2/12123287.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/532118909?book_show_action=true">Feb 10, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gina" href="/user/show/12123287-gina">Gina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer532118909" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8085193111468482748">A very moving a real story told in clear, funny, and fantastical way. Even though its set in the 1700s, the story is timeless and universal. There were turns of phrase so poignant to me that I highlighted passages (something I rarely do) and can even see myself using some of the language to describe essential human experiences in my work as a therapist. Excellently written!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


